description:
Spec 002 §Frame presets defines rich expansions for the four canonical presets:

- :test -> {:url-bound? false :fx-overrides {:rf.http/managed ... :dispatch-later ... :rf.nav/push-url ... :rf.nav/replace-url ... :rf.nav/scroll ...} :platforms #{:test} :drain-depth 100}
- :story -> {:url-bound? false :fx-overrides {:rf.http/managed ... :rf.nav/* ...} :isolation/global-state false :platforms #{:story :client}}
- :ssr-server -> {:url-bound? false :platforms #{:server} :fx-overrides {:dispatch-later ... :rf.nav/* ...} :on-create [:rf/server-init]}

The current impl in implementation/src/re_frame/frame.cljc preset-expansion only emits a tiny subset:

- :test -> {:fx-overrides {:rf.http/managed :rf.http/managed-canned-success}}
- :story -> {:fx-overrides {:rf.http/managed :rf.http/managed-canned-success} :drain-depth 16}
- :ssr-server -> {:platform :server :on-error :rf.error/server-projection}

Discrepancies to close before v0.0.1.beta (probably split into per-preset beads when work starts):

1. :test preset misses :url-bound?, :platforms #{:test}, the broader fx-overrides set (:dispatch-later, :rf.nav/*), the spec's :drain-depth 100.
2. :story preset misses :url-bound?, :platforms #{:story :client}, :isolation/global-state, the broader fx-overrides set. Current :drain-depth 16 disagrees with spec (no value spelled out in spec table; impl chose 16 as a guard).
3. :ssr-server preset uses :platform (singular) rather than :platforms #{:server}; misses :url-bound? false, the fx-overrides set, and :on-create wiring.
4. The :test/:story preset fx-overrides currently target the canonical Spec 014 :rf.http/managed (correct as of rf2-vuj5 fix). The full spec list (:dispatch-later, :rf.nav/push-url, :rf.nav/replace-url, :rf.nav/scroll) is not yet redirected.

Resolution: Either implement the rich expansions to match the spec (preferred; the spec is the contract), or trim the spec's preset tables to whatever the framework actually ships at v0.0.1. Decision should land before public v0.0.1; until then the guide describes the impl-level reality (rf2-vuj5).
